<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1420,565,1087]" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,972,604,628]" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">Identification.</emphasis>
Erect herb, 
<quantity box="[1108,1201,605,629]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="519" unit="cm" value="10.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="3.0">3–17 cm</quantity>
height, with simple and glandular hairs. Distinguished by its alternate, simple, elliptical, obovate, or ovate leaves with discoidal, extrafloral nectaries, simple hairs on both sides, 
<quantity box="[1316,1419,707,731]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="519" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="7.0">7–28 mm</quantity>
long, and 
<quantity box="[916,1017,741,765]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="519" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="4.0">4–15 mm</quantity>
wide. Flower yellow, axillary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="519" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1420,565,1087]" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,921,780,804]" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">Remarks.</emphasis>
A rare species, occurring sparsely in the native grassland. Considered Endangered in 
<collectingRegion box="[1253,1416,814,838]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1420,565,1087]" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,1000,853,878]" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest (except MS and MT states), South (
<collectingRegion box="[886,977,888,912]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="12" pageNumber="519">PR state</collectingRegion>
) and Southeast (except ES and RJ states) regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
